    "updated_at": "2014-08-06T01:51:55Z",
    "body": "Theoretically `cstring as *const u8` should work directly?\n\nI believe `c_char` is attempting to match what the platform's C compiler's do w.r.t. the signedness of chars. I think we should possibly just 'focus' these concerns into [`CString`](http://doc.rust-lang.org/master/std/c_str/struct.CString.html) rather than duplicating the null-termination handling everywhere, something like `CString::new(x, false).as_str().unwrap().to_string()` (which is a little verbose), _shrug_\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
