    "created_at": "2014-08-06T02:25:40Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-08-06T02:25:40Z",
    "body": "@huonw If we tried to match the platform C compilers means then `c_char` would be a different type on different platforms, and even different ABIs on the same architecture. For example, ARM's ABIs have unsigned `char`, whereas Apple's ABIs all have signed `char`. This isn't so bad in portable C because of the implicit numeric conversions (which are bad for other reasons), but it wouldn't work in Rust. I don't see a good reason to not make it `u8`.\n",
    "author_association": "NONE",
