    "created_at": "2014-08-07T00:51:19Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-08-07T09:21:58Z",
    "body": "c_char not being char will break sign extension in FFI code:\n\n``` c\nvoid f(int);\n\nint main(void) {\n    char c = -1;\n    f(c);\n}\n```\n\n``` rust\nfn main() {\n    let c: c_char = -1;\n    unsafe { f(c as c_int); }\n}\n```\n\nOn the same machine this will do different things if the signedness of c_char and the signedness of char don't match.\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
